just_use move.py

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: BFS desc rendering — describe_move + narrate + hint

The Python equivalent of `Game.Agent.Move.elm`'s rendering
half. Holds the per-move-desc rendering functions plus
small phrase helpers. Move descs are dataclasses
(`ExtractAbsorbDesc`, `FreePullDesc`, `PushDesc`,
`SpliceDesc`, `ShiftDesc`) — see "What it owns" below.

## Status

- **Mirrors:** `games/lynrummy/elm/src/Game/Agent/Move.elm`
  (the `describe` function family).
- **Origin:** lifted from `bfs_solver.py` 2026-04-26 as the
  module split landed.

## What it owns

- **Move desc dataclasses** (added 2026-04-26):
  `ExtractAbsorbDesc`, `FreePullDesc`, `PushDesc`,
  `SpliceDesc`, `ShiftDesc`. Each mirrors Elm's
  per-variant record under `Game.Agent.Move.elm`. They
  carry a `type` class attribute matching the legacy
  string dispatch key. Backward compat: each dataclass
  implements `__getitem__` and `get` so legacy
  `desc["foo"]` reads continue to work alongside the new
  `desc.foo` attribute access.
- `stack_label(stack)` — `" ".join(label_d(c) for c in
  stack)`. Used by every renderer.
- `describe_move(desc)` — exact structural one-line DSL
  string. Mirrors Elm's `Move.describe`.
- `narrate(desc)` — Steve-facing evocative one-liner per
  move (engulf / splice / pop / tuck …). Used by
  `agent_game.py`'s verbose log.
- `hint(desc)` — vague-but-useful player-facing nudge
  ("You can splice the 7H into a red-black run.").
- `group_kind_phrase`, `partial_kind_phrase`,
  `run_kind_phrase` — natural-language renderers for
  group + partial + run kinds. Used by `hint`.

## Migration approach (2026-04-26)

Going all-in: dataclasses replace dicts everywhere. No
backward-compat `__getitem__` shim — every read site
converts to attribute access (`desc.foo`) and every
dispatch becomes an `isinstance` check (or `match` over
the variant types). The transforms are regex-driven via
`tools/py_regex_rename.py` so the migration is repeatable
and can be reapplied if the desc shapes evolve.

Touch radius: ~133 sites across move.py + enumerator.py +
verbs.py + agent_game.py + analyze_focus_block.py + tests.
Driven by the regex tool; verified per pass against the
regression suite.

## Pointers

- Elm sibling: `games/lynrummy/elm/src/Game/Agent/Move.elm`.
